description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Give your career a positive change.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;At Cygnet Hospital Sheffield you’ll have the chance to make a real impact on patients and their families. You’ll be exposed to all kinds of new challenges and responsibilities, to ensure you continue learning and developing as you go.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Cygnet Hospital Sheffield offers low secure and locked rehabilitation services for women and CAMHS services for male and female adolescents over four distinct wards. We are currently recruiting healthcare support workers for our CAMHS service.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Working as an active member of our dynamic MDT, you’ll provide support for our nursing staff including the admission, assessment, implementation and discharge of inpatients, with a focus on dignity and safety at all times.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;You’ll bring with you a sound level of literacy and numeracy skills and preferably an NVQ level 2 in a relevant care setting. With some experience working in a secure a psychiatry service you’ll have a good level of physical fitness and a strong, flexible mental aptitude in order to meet the demands of the role. Demonstrating the abilities, experience and skills needed to deal effectively with challenging situations, you have an active interest in developing your knowledge and skills.&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; This role is on a shiftrota basis:includes working days/nights/weekends and Bank Holidays.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;In return, you’ll receive a competitive salary and a range of benefits including:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Group Pension&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;NHS Staff Discounts&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Enhanced Maternity&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Free Health Cash Plan&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Employee Referral Scheme&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;24 Hours Free GP Helpline&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Discounted Gym Membership&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Cycle To Work Scheme&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;On-site Benefits&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Free Mortgage Broker &amp; Insurance Cover&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Employee Assistance Programme (EAP&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Free Eye Tests&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Car Lease Discounts&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Paid Life Assurance Company scheme&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Smart Health Toolkit- Providing you with Fitness Programmes, Nutrition consultation and Health checks&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Please note&lt;/strong&gt;: this role is a shift pattern including weekends and nights.&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; Please note: successful candidates will be required to undergo an enhanced DBS check.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;br /&gt; Ready to make a positive change? Please click on the ‘apply now’ link below or sent an E-mail:Midlands-recruitment@cygnethealth.co.uk&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
